	h3
		b Herfindahl–Hirschman Index (HHI)
	p The index is the sum of each firm’s market share squared.
	p For a monopolist this is \(1\), for a completely competitive market it is \(0\), or \(\dfrac{1}{n}\).
	p \(H=\sum_{i=1}^ns^2_i\)
	p To normalise this between \(0\) and \(1\) we can use:
	p \(H*=\dfrac{H-\dfrac{1}{n}}{1-\dfrac{1}{n}}\)

